В§rВ§0
В§l    THE ORIGINS
В§rВ§0
В§4      в•”в•ђв•ђв•¦в•ђв•ђв•—
В§rВ§0
В§rВ§0
В§rВ§0
В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·
#- В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·
В§rВ§0
  In the first cycles
of the First Age of the
First World, when the
lands were still young
and the people new,
there was a small
chasm that many called
home. For a long time,
the people of this
В§rВ§0
В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·
#- В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·
В§rВ§0
chasm worked hard
and worked together,
content and carefree
to a fault. To their
doom.
В§rВ§0
  Darkness crept in,
unnoticed.
В§rВ§0
В§rВ§0
В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·
#- В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·
В§rВ§0
  Sensing a weakness
in the people, it mani-
fested itself within the
chasm, gaining power
and strength with each
passing day. Per-
ceiving its time had
come, the darkness
then struck hard and
В§rВ§0
В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·
#- В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·
В§rВ§0
fast, sparing none in
its way and pillaging
the chasm until only a
withered husk re-
mained.
В§rВ§0
 This was the first of
the Great Disasters of
the old days.
В§rВ§0
В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·
#- В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·
В§rВ§0
  Their home in ruins
and their population
decimated, the sur-
viving chasmfolk be-
came the founders of
many new places,
which would, in turn,
grow into homes for
many more to come.
В§rВ§0
В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·
#- В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·
В§rВ§0
  Thus, the world was
populated and the
First Age came to an
end.
В§rВ§0
В§rВ§0
В§rВ§0
В§rВ§0
В§rВ§0
В§rВ§0
