В§l  THE TRANSITION
В§rВ§0
В§4      в•”в•ђв•ђв•¦в•ђв•ђв•—
В§rВ§0
В§rВ§0
В§rВ§0
В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·
#- В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·
В§rВ§0
  It was at this point
that the Blue City and
its sister city in the
southwest reached
new heights of
success. More than
once had the dark-
ness attempted to
pillage and burn, only
В§rВ§0
В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·
#- В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·
В§rВ§0
to be fought back
each time by those who
had learned the
lessons of the chasm.
  But the darkness
is not so easily dis-
couraged.
  It used new tactics
on the Gray City in
В§rВ§0
В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·
#- В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·
В§rВ§0
the southwest, those
proud lords of the
many towers that
pierce the clouds,
poisoning their minds
with promises of power
and embroiling them in
bitter conflict.
  Watching in horror,
В§rВ§0
В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·
#- В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·
В§rВ§0
the bluefolk witnessed
their sister city tear
itself apart, its laws
abolished. The Gray
City, a place of
freedom and wealth,
was defeated.
  Unable to ignore
the symptoms in their
В§rВ§0
В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·
#- В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·
В§rВ§0
own rule of law, the
people of the Blue
City lost all hope,
abandoning their
homes and fleeing
to safe havens. The
darkness observed;
its work was complete.
  Thus, the light of
В§rВ§0
В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·
#- В§4          В·ГЇВЎГ·ВЎГЇВ·
В§rВ§0
the First Cities was
extinguished and the
Second Age came to
an end.
В§rВ§0
В§rВ§0
В§rВ§0
В§rВ§0
В§rВ§0
В§rВ§0
